Patch Set 2: (1 inline comment)

One comment inline, but it's not anything important.

I really think this should be a replacement for the checked in files though.  Trying to maintain those while also having an automated version is just going to lead to inconsistency and confusion IMHO.  I don't know that the config generator can handle split configs, but if that's a blocker to switching Glance entirely to use it, please open a bug with Oslo so we can look into how to handle that.  Thanks.

Patch Set 2:

Hello Ben,

I'd like to reply your points:

>>> Trying to maintain those while also having an automated version is just going to lead to inconsistency and confusion IMHO.

Agreed, so in PS#2 I have not checked automated version (glance.sample.conf) in, and just remained split configs. So there is no inconsistency on the configs within the trunk.

>>> I don't know that the config generator can handle split configs, but if that's a blocker to switching Glance entirely to use it, please open a bug with Oslo so we can look into how to handle that. Thanks.

I also like to see the automated version could replaces those manual version (even we could use script to generate it as needed and remove all templates from repo), but I think we concerned now on what you said here: config generator couldn't handle split configs.

Thanks.

Patch Set 2:

@Ben, as a wishlist for separated configs handling, the bug has just been created at https://bugs.launchpad.net/oslo/+bug/1300546 , IFY.

Patch Set 2:

Thanks for opening a bug on this.

I think my main concern is even having the manually maintained files.  They are going to be perpetually out of date so we need to get away from doing that, and as long as they're checked in to the git repo people are going to use them even if we provide this also.

Patch Set 2: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

I'd like to move this forward. I also think this is -rc2 worthy. Mark, Zhi Yan any thoughts?

I don't want to cut -rc2 with an outdated config file.
